# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SmartCare API — REST Client Test Suite
# Extension required: humao.rest-client (VS Code REST Client)
# Run order: top to bottom. Never skip a group that a later group depends on.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── STATIC VARIABLES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: baseUrl is port 5027 (from Properties/launchSettings.json), not 5000
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5027
@adminEmail = admin@smartcare.com
@adminPassword = Admin@1234
@doctorEmail = doctor@smartcare.com-+
/ 
@doctorPassword = Doctor@1234
@patientEmail = suraj2005jan@gmail.com
@patientPhone = 9876543210

# ── UPDATE THESE DATES BEFORE RUNNING ─────────────────────────────────────────
# tomorrowDate  = any future date (used as appointment booking date)
# futureDatePlus2 = a different future date (used for reschedule target & completion)
# pastDate      = any date in the past (used to test date validation)
@tomorrowDate = 2026-12-18
@futureDatePlus2 = 2026-12-20
@pastDate = 2020-01-01

# ── PASTE THESE AFTER RUNNING THE RELEVANT REQUESTS ───────────────────────────
# Do not fill these in now — they come from API responses at runtime
@adminToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..xtf9dIMSBdEDVClZDgQabHhgDR83W0XYtT2VO-S9V6Y
@doctorToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..qzldskqbQb6YsYwSDDwf1k_OPqKFA92zH7zmsGOHHBU
@doctorId = 6a033fee09555109ab6edc1a
@drVinayaId = PASTE_AFTER_STEP_2.3
@appointmentId = PASTE_AFTER_STEP_3.1
@appointmentIdConfirm = PASTE_FRESH_FOR_GROUP_5
@appointmentIdCancel = PASTE_FRESH_FOR_GROUP_6
@appointmentIdReschedule = PASTE_FRESH_FOR_GROUP_7
@testimonialId = PASTE_AFTER_STEP_9.1
@newAppointmentId = PASTE_FROM_RESCHEDULE_RESPONSE


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 1 — AUTHENTICATION (Part 1: Admin Setup)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Run steps 1.1–1.3 first, then run all of GROUP 2,
### then return here for steps 1.4–1.8 (Doctor user setup).

### Step 1.1 — Register Admin account — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}",
  "role": "Admin"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — body: { id, email, role: "Admin" }
# ❌ If you see 409: admin@smartcare.com already registered — delete from MongoDB users collection and re-run
# ⚠️  IDEMPOTENT: Will fail with 409 on re-run
# To re-run: manually delete the admin user from MongoDB Atlas (users collection)

###

### Step 1.2 — Duplicate registration (same email) — Expect: 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}",
  "role": "Admin"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: same email as step 1.1 — should be rejected
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "An account with this email already exists" }
# ❌ If you see 201: duplicate check in AuthController is not running

###

### Step 1.3 — Login Admin — Expect: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — body: { token, email, role: "Admin", expiresIn }
# ❌ If you see 401: wrong credentials or admin not registered — run step 1.1 first

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "token" from the response above
# Paste it into @adminToken at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### ── PAUSE HERE — Run all of GROUP 2 before continuing to step 1.4 ──────────


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 2 — DOCTORS
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Prerequisite: @adminToken must be set from step 1.3

### Step 2.1 — Seed doctors (Admin) — Expect: 200
# ⚠️  IDEMPOTENT: Returns "Database already seeded" if doctors already exist
# To re-seed: drop the doctors collection in MongoDB Atlas
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/seed
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — body: { "message": "Seeded 2 doctors successfully" }
#             OR:  { "message": "Database already seeded" } on re-run
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken not set — complete step 1.3 first

###

### Step 2.2 — Seed again (idempotency check) — Expect: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/seed
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — body: { "message": "Database already seeded" }
# ❌ If you see "Seeded 2 doctors": seed is not checking count before inserting
# AUTH LEVEL: Admin token — Expect: 200

###

### Step 2.3 — Get all doctors — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors

# ✅ Expect: 200 — array of 2+ doctors:
#   [0] Dr. Varun Prasanna, Orthopaedics, slots: 09:00–11:30
#   [1] Dr. Vinaya Prasanna, Gynaecology, slots: 14:00–16:30
# ❌ If you see []: seed was not run — complete step 2.1 first

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From the response array:
#   Copy "id" of Dr. Varun Prasanna  → paste into @doctorId at the top
#   Copy "id" of Dr. Vinaya Prasanna → paste into @drVinayaId at the top
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 2.4 — Get doctor by ID — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/{{doctorId}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — Dr. Varun Prasanna, Orthopaedics, availableSlots: ["09:00","09:30","10:00","10:30","11:00","11:30"]
# ❌ If you see 404: @doctorId not set — re-run step 2.3 and paste the ID

###

### Step 2.5 — Get doctor by non-existent ID — Expect: 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/000000000000000000000000

# ✅ Expect: 404 — body: { "error": "Doctor not found" }
# ❌ If you see 200: ObjectId collision (extremely unlikely) — use a different fake ID

###

### Step 2.6 — Create custom doctor (Admin) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Arjun Mehta",
  "specialty": "Cardiology",
  "availableSlots": ["10:00", "11:00", "12:00"]
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — body contains new doctor with generated id, name, specialty, availableSlots
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken not set — complete step 1.3 first

###

### Step 2.7 — Create doctor without auth — Expect: 401
# AUTH LEVEL: None — Expect: 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Unauthorized",
  "specialty": "None",
  "availableSlots": ["09:00"]
}

# ✅ Expect: 401 — no token provided; [Authorize(Roles="Admin")] blocks the request
# ❌ If you see 201: Authorization middleware is not active — check Program.cs

###

### Step 2.8 — Create doctor with Doctor token (wrong role) — Expect: 403
# AUTH LEVEL: Doctor token — Expect: 403
# ⚠️  Run steps 1.4–1.6 before this step to obtain @doctorToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Forbidden",
  "specialty": "None",
  "availableSlots": ["09:00"]
}

# ✅ Expect: 403 — Doctor role cannot create doctors; only Admin can
# ❌ If you see 201: Role-based authorization is misconfigured

###

### Step 2.9 — Create doctor with missing required fields — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "specialty": "",
  "availableSlots": []
}

# CHANGE from happy path: name and specialty are empty strings
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Doctor Name and Specialty are required" }
# ❌ If you see 201: controller validation guard is not running


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 1 — AUTHENTICATION (Part 2: Doctor User Setup)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Prerequisite: @doctorId must be set from step 2.3

### Step 1.4 — Register Doctor user account — Expect: 201
# ⚠️  IDEMPOTENT: Will fail with 409 if doctor@smartcare.com already registered
# To re-run: manually delete the doctor user from MongoDB Atlas (users collection)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{doctorEmail}}",
  "password": "{{doctorPassword}}",
  "role": "Doctor",
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — body: { id, email, role: "Doctor" }
# ❌ If you see 400 (validation failed): @doctorId not set — complete step 2.3 first
# ❌ If you see 409: doctor@smartcare.com already registered — delete from users collection

###

### Step 1.5 — Validation: short password — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "shortpass@test.com",
  "password": "abc",
  "role": "Admin"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: password is "abc" (3 chars) — MinLength(8) should reject
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Validation failed", "fields": { "Password": ["Password must be at least 8 characters"] } }
# ❌ If you see 201: [MinLength(8)] on RegisterDto.Password is not active

###

### Step 1.6 — Login Doctor — Expect: 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{doctorEmail}}",
  "password": "{{doctorPassword}}"
}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — body: { token, email, role: "Doctor", expiresIn }
# ❌ If you see 401: doctor user not registered — run step 1.4 first

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "token" from the response above
# Paste it into @doctorToken at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 1.7 — Validation: invalid role value — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "patient@test.com",
  "password": "Secure@123",
  "role": "Patient"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: role is "Patient" — [AllowedValues("Admin","Doctor")] should reject
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Validation failed", "fields": { "Role": ["Role must be Admin or Doctor"] } }
# ❌ If you see 201: [AllowedValues] constraint on RegisterDto.Role is not active

###

### Step 1.8 — Login with wrong password — Expect: 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword!"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: password is incorrect
# ✅ Expect: 401 — body: { "error": "Invalid email or password" }
# ❌ If you see 200: BCrypt.Verify is not being called in AuthController.Login


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 3 — BOOK APPOINTMENTS
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Prerequisite: @doctorId set (step 2.3). No auth required — public endpoint.
### @patientEmail must be a real inbox you can check for booking confirmation.

### Step 3.1 — Book appointment (happy path) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Ravi Kumar",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "09:00",
  "notes": "First visit, knee pain since 3 months",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Self",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — appointment object, status: "Pending", id populated
# ❌ If you see 400 "date must be today or in the future": update @tomorrowDate to a future date
# ❌ If you see 409: slot 09:00 on @tomorrowDate already booked — use a different slot

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "id" from the response above
# Paste it into @appointmentId at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment — We'll See You Soon"
# Body must contain: "Appointment Request Received"
# Tone: booking
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 3.2 — Book with past date — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Ravi Kumar",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{pastDate}}",
  "slot": "09:00",
  "notes": "",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Self",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: date is "{{pastDate}}" (2020-01-01) — past date
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Appointment date must be today or in the future" }
# ❌ If you see 201: past-date guard in AppointmentsController.Create is not running

###

### Step 3.3 — Book with invalid slot format — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Ravi Kumar",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "9:00 AM",
  "notes": "",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Self",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: slot is "9:00 AM" instead of "09:00" (24-hr HH:MM required)
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Slot must be in HH:MM 24-hour format (e.g. 09:00)" }
# ❌ If you see 201: SlotFormatRegex in the controller is not matching

###

### Step 3.4 — Book with slot not in doctor's schedule — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Ravi Kumar",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "08:00",
  "notes": "",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Self",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: slot "08:00" is not in Dr. Varun's schedule (09:00–11:30 only)
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "The slot 08:00 is not in this doctor's available hours" }
# ❌ If you see 201: availableSlots.Contains check is not running

###

### Step 3.5 — Duplicate slot conflict (same doctor + date + slot) — Expect: 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Different Patient",
  "patientPhone": "9000000001",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "09:00",
  "notes": "Trying to book same slot as step 3.1",
  "patientType": "Returning",
  "referralSource": "DoctorReferral",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: same doctorId + date + slot as step 3.1 — should conflict
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "This slot is already booked. Please choose a different time." }
# ❌ If you see 201: SlotTakenAsync check in the repository is not working

###

### Step 3.6 — Book with invalid doctorId — Expect: 404
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "000000000000000000000000",
  "patientName": "Ravi Kumar",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "09:00",
  "notes": "",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Self",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: doctorId is a fake ObjectId that does not exist
# ✅ Expect: 404 — body: { "error": "Doctor not found. Please select a valid doctor." }
# ❌ If you see 201: GetByIdAsync is not being called to validate the doctor

###

### Step 3.7 — Book with missing required fields — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "",
  "patientName": "",
  "patientPhone": "",
  "patientEmail": "not-an-email",
  "date": "",
  "slot": "",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Self",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: doctorId, patientName, patientPhone, date, slot are all empty; patientEmail is invalid
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Validation failed", "fields": { "DoctorId": [...], "PatientName": [...], ... } }
# ❌ If you see 201: [Required] annotations on CreateAppointmentDto are not active


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 4 — ADMIN: VIEW APPOINTMENTS
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Prerequisite: @adminToken, @doctorToken, @appointmentId, @doctorId all set.

### Step 4.1 — Get all upcoming appointments (Admin) — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — array containing at least the appointment from step 3.1 (status: "Pending")
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken not set or expired — re-run step 1.3
# ❌ If you see empty []: step 3.1 not yet run

###

### Step 4.2 — Get all appointments including past (Admin) — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments?includePast=true
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — array including appointments from all dates (past + future)
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken expired — re-run step 1.3

###

### Step 4.3 — Get appointment by ID (Admin) — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — full appointment object, status: "Pending", patientName: "Ravi Kumar"
# ❌ If you see 404: @appointmentId not set — complete step 3.1 and paste the id

###

### Step 4.4 — Get appointment by ID (Doctor token) — Expect: 200
# AUTH LEVEL: Doctor token — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — same appointment object; Doctor role has read access on GET /{id}
# ❌ If you see 403: Doctor role is incorrectly excluded from this endpoint

###

### Step 4.5 — Get appointments by doctor (Admin) — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/doctor/{{doctorId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — array of appointments for Dr. Varun Prasanna; includes step 3.1 booking
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken expired — re-run step 1.3

###

### Step 4.6 — Get appointments by doctor including past (Doctor token) — Expect: 200
# AUTH LEVEL: Doctor token — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/doctor/{{doctorId}}?includePast=true
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — Doctor can view their own schedule including past appointments
# ❌ If you see 403: Doctor role incorrectly excluded from GET /doctor/{doctorId}

###

### Step 4.7 — Get all appointments without auth — Expect: 401
# AUTH LEVEL: None — Expect: 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments

# ✅ Expect: 401 — [Authorize(Roles="Admin")] blocks unauthenticated requests
# ❌ If you see 200: Authorization is not wired up in Program.cs

###

### Step 4.8 — Get appointment by ID without auth — Expect: 401
# AUTH LEVEL: None — Expect: 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}

# ✅ Expect: 401 — [Authorize(Roles="Admin,Doctor")] blocks unauthenticated requests
# ❌ If you see 200: [Authorize] attribute is missing on GetById


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 5 — CONFIRM APPOINTMENT
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── REQUIRES FRESH APPOINTMENT ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Book a new appointment before running this group (step 5.1 does this for you)
# Update @appointmentIdConfirm at the top with the id from step 5.1
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Step 5.1 — Book fresh appointment for confirmation (slot 09:30) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Priya Sharma",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "09:30",
  "notes": "Follow-up physiotherapy check",
  "patientType": "Returning",
  "referralSource": "HospitalReferral",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — new appointment with status: "Pending"
# ❌ If you see 409: slot 09:30 on @tomorrowDate is taken — change the slot in the body

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "id" from the response above
# Paste it into @appointmentIdConfirm at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment — We'll See You Soon"
# Body must contain: "Appointment Request Received"
# Tone: booking
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 5.2 — Update status to Confirmed (Admin) — Expect: 204
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdConfirm}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Confirmed"
}

# ✅ Expect: 204 No Content — status updated; confirmation email sent to patient
# ❌ If you see 404: @appointmentIdConfirm not set — complete step 5.1 first
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken expired — re-run step 1.3

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Appointment Confirmed — See You on {{tomorrowDate}}"
# Body must contain: "your appointment has been confirmed"
# Tone: confirmed
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 5.3 — Verify appointment is now Confirmed — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdConfirm}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — appointment with status: "Confirmed"
# ❌ If you see status "Pending": PATCH in step 5.2 did not persist to MongoDB

###

### Step 5.4 — Confirm appointment using Doctor token — Expect: 204
# AUTH LEVEL: Doctor token — Expect: 204
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Confirmed"
}

# ✅ Expect: 204 — Doctor role is allowed to update status per [Authorize(Roles="Admin,Doctor")]
# ❌ If you see 403: Doctor role is incorrectly excluded from PATCH /{id}/status


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 6 — ADMIN CANCEL APPOINTMENT
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── REQUIRES FRESH APPOINTMENT ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Book a new appointment before running this group (step 6.1 does this for you)
# Update @appointmentIdCancel at the top with the id from step 6.1
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Step 6.1 — Book fresh appointment for admin cancel (slot 10:00) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Anand Naik",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "10:00",
  "notes": "Annual orthopaedic check-up",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "Other",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — new appointment with status: "Pending"
# ❌ If you see 409: slot 10:00 is already taken — change to an unused slot

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "id" from the response above
# Paste it into @appointmentIdCancel at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment — We'll See You Soon"
# Body must contain: "Appointment Request Received"
# Tone: booking
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 6.2 — Admin cancels appointment with reason — Expect: 204
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdCancel}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Cancelled",
  "cancelledBy": "Admin",
  "cancellationReason": "Doctor unavailable due to a medical emergency — sincere apologies for the inconvenience"
}

# ✅ Expect: 204 No Content — appointment cancelled; admin-cancellation email sent to patient
# ❌ If you see 404: @appointmentIdCancel not set — complete step 6.1 first
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken expired — re-run step 1.3

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment Has Been Cancelled"
# Body must contain: "cancelled by the hospital due to unforeseen circumstances"
# Tone: cancelled-admin
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 6.3 — Verify appointment is Cancelled — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdCancel}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 200 — status: "Cancelled", cancelledBy: "Admin", cancellationReason populated
# ❌ If you see status "Pending": PATCH in step 6.2 did not persist

###

### Step 6.4 — Try to patient-cancel an already-admin-cancelled appointment — Expect: 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/patient-cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{appointmentIdCancel}}",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "reason": "I also want to cancel this appointment"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: appointment is already Cancelled (from step 6.2)
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "This appointment is already cancelled" }
# ❌ If you see 200: already-cancelled guard in PatientCancel is not running

###

### Step 6.5 — Cancel without auth — Expect: 401
# AUTH LEVEL: None — Expect: 401
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdCancel}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Cancelled",
  "cancelledBy": "Admin",
  "cancellationReason": "Unauthorized attempt"
}

# ✅ Expect: 401 — PATCH /{id}/status requires Admin or Doctor token
# ❌ If you see 204: [Authorize] is missing on UpdateStatus


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### GROUP 7 — RESCHEDULE APPOINTMENT
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── REQUIRES FRESH APPOINTMENT ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Book a new appointment before running this group (step 7.1 does this for you)
# Update @appointmentIdReschedule at the top with the id from step 7.1
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Step 7.1 — Book fresh appointment for reschedule (slot 11:00) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "patientName": "Kavya Reddy",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "patientEmail": "{{patientEmail}}",
  "date": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "slot": "11:00",
  "notes": "Joint pain assessment",
  "patientType": "New",
  "referralSource": "DoctorReferral",
  "appointmentType": "OPD"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — new appointment with status: "Pending"
# ❌ If you see 409: slot 11:00 on @tomorrowDate is taken — use slot 11:30

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "id" from the response above
# Paste it into @appointmentIdReschedule at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment — We'll See You Soon"
# Body must contain: "Appointment Request Received"
# Tone: booking
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 7.2 — Reschedule appointment (Admin) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdReschedule}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{appointmentIdReschedule}}",
  "newDate": "{{futureDatePlus2}}",
  "newSlot": "09:00",
  "reason": "Doctor requested a slot change to accommodate an emergency case"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — body: { message, originalAppointmentId, newAppointment { id, ... } }
#             Two emails sent: admin-cancellation for old appointment + booking for new
# ❌ If you see 404: @appointmentIdReschedule not set — complete step 7.1 first
# ❌ If you see 409: slot 09:00 on @futureDatePlus2 is taken — use a different newSlot

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "newAppointment.id" from the response above
# Paste it into @newAppointmentId at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Email 1 Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment Has Been Cancelled"
# Email 1 Body must contain: "cancelled by the hospital due to unforeseen circumstances"
# Tone: cancelled-admin (for the original appointment)
# Email 2 Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment — We'll See You Soon"
# Email 2 Body must contain: "Appointment Request Received"
# Tone: booking (for the new rescheduled appointment)
# Check inbox within 30 seconds — expect 2 emails
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 7.3 — Try to reschedule a cancelled appointment — Expect: 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentIdCancel}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{appointmentIdCancel}}",
  "newDate": "{{futureDatePlus2}}",
  "newSlot": "09:30",
  "reason": "Trying to reschedule a cancelled appointment"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: @appointmentIdCancel was cancelled in step 6.2
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "Cannot reschedule a cancelled appointment" }
# ❌ If you see 201: cancelled-appointment guard in Reschedule is not running

###

### Step 7.4 — Reschedule to a past date — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{newAppointmentId}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{newAppointmentId}}",
  "newDate": "{{pastDate}}",
  "newSlot": "09:00",
  "reason": "Trying to reschedule to past date"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: newDate is "{{pastDate}}" (2020-01-01) — in the past
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "New appointment date must be today or in the future" }
# ❌ If you see 201: past-date guard in Reschedule is not running

###

### Step 7.5 — Reschedule with invalid slot format — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{newAppointmentId}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{newAppointmentId}}",
  "newDate": "{{futureDatePlus2}}",
  "newSlot": "9AM",
  "reason": "Slot format test"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: newSlot is "9AM" instead of HH:MM 24-hour format
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "NewSlot must be in HH:MM 24-hour format (e.g. 09:00)" }
# ❌ If you see 201: SlotFormatRegex is not being applied in Reschedule

###

### Step 7.6 — Reschedule to an already-taken slot — Expect: 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{newAppointmentId}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{newAppointmentId}}",
  "newDate": "{{tomorrowDate}}",
  "newSlot": "09:00",
  "reason": "Trying to take a slot already booked in step 3.1"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: slot 09:00 on @tomorrowDate is already taken by step 3.1
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "Slot 09:00 on ... is already booked. Please choose a different time." }
# ❌ If you see 201: SlotTakenAsync is not being checked in Reschedule

###

### Step 7.7 — Reschedule using Doctor token — Expect: 201
# AUTH LEVEL: Doctor token — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{newAppointmentId}}/reschedule
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{newAppointmentId}}",
  "newDate": "{{futureDatePlus2}}",
  "newSlot": "09:30",
  "reason": "Doctor rescheduling to a preferred time slot"
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — Doctor role can reschedule; two emails sent
# ❌ If you see 403: Doctor role incorrectly excluded from POST /{id}/reschedule

# ── EMAIL CHECK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Email 1 Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment Has Been Cancelled"
# Tone: cancelled-admin (for the appointment being replaced)
# Email 2 Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment — We'll See You Soon"
# Tone: booking (for the newly created appointment)
# Check inbox within 30 seconds — expect 2 emails
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


