# Sender: appointmentnotif.spandana@gmail.com
# Subject: "Your SmartCare Appointment Has Been Cancelled"
# Body must contain: "successfully cancelled as requested"
# Tone: cancelled-patient
# Check inbox within 30 seconds of sending this request
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 8.4 — Try to patient-cancel an already-cancelled appointment — Expect: 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/patient-cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{appointmentId}}",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "reason": "Trying to cancel an already cancelled appointment"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: appointment was cancelled in step 8.3
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "This appointment is already cancelled" }
# ❌ If you see 200: already-cancelled guard is not running

###

### Step 8.5 — Patient cancel with wrong phone number — Expect: 404
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/patient-cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{appointmentId}}",
  "patientPhone": "0000000000",
  "reason": "Testing ownership check"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: patientPhone is wrong — does not match the appointment
# ✅ Expect: 404 — body: { "error": "No appointment found with this ID and phone number" }
# ❌ If you see 200: GetByIdAndPhoneAsync ownership check is not working

###

### Step 8.6 — Patient cancel with reason too short — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/patient-cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "{{appointmentId}}",
  "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
  "reason": "No"
}

# CHANGE from happy path: reason is "No" (2 chars) — MinLength(5) should reject
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Validation failed", "fields": { "Reason": ["Please provide a reason for cancellation"] } }
# ❌ If you see 200: [MinLength(5)] on PatientCancelDto.Reason is not active

###

### Step 8.7 — Lookup with missing appointment ID param — Expect: 400
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/lookup?phone={{patientPhone}}

# CHANGE from happy path: id query param is absent
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Appointment ID is required" }
# ❌ If you see 404: id-required guard in Lookup is not running

###

### Step 8.8 — Lookup with missing phone param — Expect: 400
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/lookup?id={{appointmentId}}

# CHANGE from happy path: phone query param is absent
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Phone number is required" }
# ❌ If you see 404: phone-required guard in Lookup is not running

###

### Step 8.9 — Lookup with wrong ID + phone combination — Expect: 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/lookup?id=000000000000000000000000&phone={{patientPhone}}

# CHANGE from happy path: id does not match any appointment for this phone
# ✅ Expect: 404 — body: { "error": "No appointment found with this ID and phone number" }
# ❌ If you see 200: GetByIdAndPhoneAsync is not filtering by both fields

###

### Step 8.10 — Patient cancel within 24 hours — Expect: 409
# ⚠️  MANUAL SETUP REQUIRED: This test requires a near-future appointment.
# To test: create an appointment for today's date at a time within the next 24 hours.
# Then run patient-cancel against it. The test below uses a placeholder id.
# This cannot be reliably hardcoded — run it manually when needed.
#
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/patient-cancel
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "appointmentId": "REPLACE_WITH_NEAR_FUTURE_APPOINTMENT_ID",
#   "patientPhone": "{{patientPhone}}",
#   "reason": "Need to cancel urgently"
# }
#
# ✅ Expect: 409 — body: { "error": "Cancellations must be made at least 24 hours before the appointment..." }


