### GROUP 9 — TESTIMONIALS
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Public submission; approval requires Admin token.

### Step 9.1 — Submit testimonial (public) — Expect: 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientName": "Ravi Kumar",
  "text": "Excellent experience at SmartCare. Dr. Varun Prasanna was thorough and very professional. The staff was courteous and the appointment was on time.",
  "rating": 5
}

# ✅ Expect: 201 — testimonial object with isApproved: false, id populated
# ❌ If you see 400: missing required fields or rating out of range

# ── CAPTURE REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy "id" from the response above
# Paste it into @testimonialId at the top of this file
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### Step 9.2 — Get approved testimonials (none approved yet) — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials

# ✅ Expect: 200 — empty array [] (the testimonial from step 9.1 is not yet approved)
# ❌ If you see the step 9.1 testimonial: isApproved defaults to true — check Testimonial model

###

### Step 9.3 — Submit with rating out of range — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientName": "Test Patient",
  "text": "Testing rating validation",
  "rating": 6
}

# CHANGE from happy path: rating is 6 — [Range(1, 5)] should reject
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Validation failed", "fields": { "Rating": ["Rating must be between 1 and 5"] } }
# ❌ If you see 201: [Range(1,5)] on CreateTestimonialDto.Rating is not active

###

### Step 9.4 — Submit with missing required fields — Expect: 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientName": "",
  "text": "",
  "rating": 0
}

# CHANGE from happy path: all fields empty or zero — [Required] and [Range] should reject
# ✅ Expect: 400 — body: { "error": "Validation failed", "fields": { ... } }
# ❌ If you see 201: [Required] annotations on CreateTestimonialDto are not active

###

### Step 9.5 — Approve testimonial (Admin) — Expect: 204
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials/{{testimonialId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 204 No Content — testimonial approved; isApproved set to true
# ❌ If you see 404: @testimonialId not set — complete step 9.1 and paste the id
# ❌ If you see 401: @adminToken expired — re-run step 1.3

###

### Step 9.6 — Get approved testimonials (now has one) — Expect: 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials

# ✅ Expect: 200 — array containing the testimonial from step 9.1 (isApproved: true)
# ❌ If you see []: PATCH in step 9.5 did not persist to MongoDB

###

### Step 9.7 — Approve non-existent testimonial — Expect: 404
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials/000000000000000000000000/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 404 — body: { "error": "Testimonial not found" }
# ❌ If you see 204: GetByIdAsync is not being called before ApproveAsync

###

### Step 9.8 — Approve testimonial without auth — Expect: 401
# AUTH LEVEL: None — Expect: 401
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials/{{testimonialId}}/approve

# ✅ Expect: 401 — [Authorize(Roles="Admin")] blocks unauthenticated requests
# ❌ If you see 204: [Authorize] is missing on the Approve action

###

### Step 9.9 — Approve testimonial with Doctor token (wrong role) — Expect: 403
# AUTH LEVEL: Doctor token — Expect: 403
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/testimonials/{{testimonialId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

# ✅ Expect: 403 — Doctor role cannot approve testimonials
# ❌ If you see 204: Role check on Approve is not restricting to Admin-only


