### ── NOTES AND SETUP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PREREQUISITES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • Install the VS Code REST Client extension: humao.rest-client
# • Start the API: dotnet run (from the SmartCare.API directory)
# • API runs on http://localhost:5027 (see Properties/launchSettings.json)
# • MongoDB Atlas must be running and credentials set in appsettings.json
#
# BEFORE EACH TEST RUN
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • Set @patientEmail to a real inbox you can check for email notifications
# • Update @tomorrowDate to any future date (e.g., next month)
# • Update @futureDatePlus2 to a different future date after @tomorrowDate
# • All @...Token and @...Id variables start as placeholders — paste after running
#
# RUN ORDER
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Run strictly top to bottom. Never skip a group that a later group depends on.
# Dependency chain:
#   1.1–1.3 (admin) → 2.1–2.3 (doctors + capture IDs) → 1.4–1.8 (doctor user)
#   → 3.1 (book, capture appointmentId) → 4.x (view)
#   → 5.1 (book fresh, capture appointmentIdConfirm) → 5.x (confirm)
#   → 6.1 (book fresh, capture appointmentIdCancel) → 6.x (admin cancel)
#   → 7.1 (book fresh, capture appointmentIdReschedule) → 7.x (reschedule)
#   → 8.x (patient cancel) → 9.x (testimonials) → 10.x (complete) → 11.x (noshow)
#
# STEPS THAT REQUIRE MANUAL DATABASE CLEANUP BEFORE RE-RUNNING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
